WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.281
Previously on "Stumptown"...

00:03.290 --> 00:04.029
I'm coming out
of a long-term thing.

00:04.040 --> 00:05.450
What, like parole?

00:05.460 --> 00:07.075
How long were you
guys together?
Four years.

00:07.080 --> 00:08.786
But also,
I really did do time.

00:08.790 --> 00:10.951
I need to get my 1,500 hours
of apprenticeship

00:10.960 --> 00:12.496
so I can be certified
here in Oregon.

00:12.500 --> 00:14.240
You're green,
but you could be good, Dex.

00:14.250 --> 00:16.241
Why is Hoffman
asking about you

00:16.250 --> 00:17.706
and a dead guy
named Jack Feeney?

00:17.710 --> 00:20.247
Feeney was in prison
with Grey McConnell.

00:20.250 --> 00:22.571
Guess who else was on his tier.
Wallace Kane.

00:22.580 --> 00:25.208
Feeney ends up dead.
A week later, Kane breaks out.

00:25.210 --> 00:26.950
I need a whiskey...

00:26.960 --> 00:28.279
and a good chiropractor.

00:28.290 --> 00:30.110
Kane is planning something
here in Portland.

00:30.120 --> 00:31.576
He's got
some unfinished business.

00:31.580 --> 00:33.241
How do you know this?
Because I'm in his head!

00:33.250 --> 00:35.662
Do you remember
that trip to Hawaii

00:35.670 --> 00:36.785
that you wouldn't
shut up about?

00:36.790 --> 00:37.870
Take it.

00:37.880 --> 00:39.370
I put Wallace Kane away.

00:39.380 --> 00:41.530
IfI was under his thumb,
I'd be afraid.

00:41.540 --> 00:42.700
Aah!

00:42.710 --> 00:44.246
[ Grunting ]

00:44.250 --> 00:46.036
You owe me
a half a million dollars.

00:48.000 --> 00:49.991
[Air horn blows ]

00:50.000 --> 00:51.706
[ Sports announcer
speaking indistinctly ]

00:51.710 --> 00:53.530
[ Whistle blows ]

00:53.540 --> 00:54.529
Don't say it.

00:54.540 --> 00:55.575
You look funny.

00:55.580 --> 00:56.740
[ Chuckles ]

00:56.750 --> 00:58.411
Finish your Pop-Tarts, okay?

00:58.420 --> 00:59.956
Blueberry is better.

00:59.960 --> 01:02.167
Well,
pumpkin was on sale.

01:02.170 --> 01:03.910
Why are you dressed
like that?

01:03.920 --> 01:05.160
I'm trying
to look professional.

01:05.170 --> 01:06.990
I have a very important
meeting today.

01:07.000 --> 01:08.911
With who?

01:08.920 --> 01:11.787
Uh, Janet Withers,
um, from the DPSST,

01:11.790 --> 01:13.746
the Department of Public

01:13.750 --> 01:15.411
something or something,
whatever.

01:15.420 --> 01:16.660
So you can be a P.I.?

01:16.670 --> 01:17.659
Yeah. Yeah.

01:17.670 --> 01:19.319
If I get my certification,

01:19.330 --> 01:24.165
that means blueberry Pop-Tarts
all day, any day.

01:24.170 --> 01:25.376
Okay,
can you turn this off?

01:25.380 --> 01:26.415
[Video game beeps,
controller clatters ]

01:26.420 --> 01:27.705
I'm gonna drop you off
at the bar.

01:27.710 --> 01:29.871
Did you try Grey to let him know
we're on our way?

01:29.880 --> 01:31.074
He didn't pick up.
Okay.

01:31.080 --> 01:32.286
Well, he's probably busy.

01:32.290 --> 01:33.325
He always picks up.

01:33.330 --> 01:34.706
We'll try him on the way,
alright?

01:34.710 --> 01:36.246
Come on.

01:36.250 --> 01:38.036
So, we got to break
into the vault

01:38.040 --> 01:39.610
and then bust
into the safe?

01:39.620 --> 01:41.952
That's a two-day job.
Right, Grey?

01:41.960 --> 01:43.370
How should I know?

01:43.380 --> 01:44.574
I haven't even
seen the thing.

01:46.120 --> 01:48.327
I'm not going
back to prison for Kane.

01:48.330 --> 01:49.911
Will you guys help me
ifI pump the brakes here?

01:49.920 --> 01:51.876
Hell, yeah.

01:51.880 --> 01:53.916
This is nuts.

01:55.210 --> 01:56.450
Come on.
Both of you guys chill.

01:56.460 --> 01:57.950
Look, you know
I got no beef with you,

01:57.960 --> 01:59.166
but I'm looking out
for myself.

01:59.170 --> 02:03.118
Gentlemen...
we're In busmess.

02:03.120 --> 02:06.169
10 years ago,
I started a beautiful tunnel.

02:06.170 --> 02:08.536
Amazingly,
it's still intact.

02:08.540 --> 02:11.452
So, basically, we are
on the 5-yard line.

02:11.460 --> 02:13.997
We will be in Las Vegas
by midnight,

02:14.000 --> 02:17.208
at which point in time,
I will be in libertine mode.

02:17.210 --> 02:20.373
[Jackhammer rattles
in distance ]

02:20.380 --> 02:21.699
What?

02:21.710 --> 02:24.201
The boys and I
have been talking.

02:24.210 --> 02:26.496
I love
where this is headed.

02:26.500 --> 02:28.161
Why're we rushing
this thing?

02:33.290 --> 02:34.575
Ugh!

02:34.580 --> 02:37.037
[ Grunting ]

02:37.040 --> 02:40.168
[ Hank coughs, groans ]

02:41.670 --> 02:44.616
Good question.

02:44.620 --> 02:45.917
The reason we're rushing

02:45.920 --> 02:47.456
is because _
I'm an escaped conVIct,

02:47.460 --> 02:49.371
and it's not really
in my best interest

02:49.380 --> 02:51.029
to spend too much time
in any one location.

02:51.040 --> 02:52.701
I mean, I would love

02:52.710 --> 02:55.281
to just chill here in Portland
for a few weeks,

02:55.290 --> 02:57.201
hit up some microbreweries,

02:57.210 --> 02:58.609
but that's just
not in the cards.

02:58.620 --> 03:02.989
So, anyone else have anything
to share with the group?

03:05.170 --> 03:08.662
Comments?

03:08.670 --> 03:12.037
Concerns?

03:12.040 --> 03:13.200
Greyson?

03:14.210 --> 03:17.327
Are you done
shaking your ass, man?

03:17.330 --> 03:18.740
'Cause apparently,
I got a job to do,

03:18.750 --> 03:19.739
and I'd like to do it.

03:19.750 --> 03:21.069
I'm sick of watching this.

03:24.120 --> 03:26.611
He's the only one
I let talk to me like that.

03:28.710 --> 03:30.496
I don't know why.

03:32.670 --> 03:34.740
Move your ass.

03:34.750 --> 03:35.739
[ Siren wails ]

03:41.380 --> 03:43.996
[ Lock disengages ]

03:44.000 --> 03:45.115
Grey.

03:45.120 --> 03:45.996
Grey.

03:46.000 --> 03:47.410
Grey, are you here?

03:47.420 --> 03:49.069
Well, he probably overslept.
Let me call him.

03:49.080 --> 03:50.411
[ Cellphone chimes ]

03:50.420 --> 03:51.489
Oh, look,
I have a voicemail from him.

03:51.500 --> 03:54.162
You never
check your messages.

03:54.170 --> 03:56.411
Grey:
Dex, I hate to lay this on you,
but I had an emergency.

03:56.420 --> 03:58.536
M-My aunt in Houston
is really sick.

03:58.540 --> 04:00.701
I had to catch a flight
last minute.

04:00.710 --> 04:02.530
Look, can you watch the bar
until I get back?

04:02.540 --> 04:03.825
A few days, tops.

04:03.830 --> 04:05.240
Your brother will show you
what to do.

04:05.250 --> 04:06.376
Please. I owe you.
[ Sighs ]

04:06.380 --> 04:07.415
Aunt? What aunt?

04:07.420 --> 04:09.456
He has a_ --
He has a cousm In Tacoma,

04:09.460 --> 04:11.451
an uncle in, um --
in Connecticut,

04:11.460 --> 04:13.576
but I've never heard of
an aunt In Houston.

04:13.580 --> 04:15.036
We open in an hour.

04:15.040 --> 04:18.669
"We"? Buddy, I have
an interview to go to, okay?

04:18.670 --> 04:20.240
I need help.

04:21.710 --> 04:23.200
Yeah. Okay.

04:23.210 --> 04:26.532
Uh, maybe Janet Withers
can come here.

04:26.540 --> 04:27.950
Right?

04:27.960 --> 04:29.109
So, what should
we do first?

04:29.120 --> 04:31.076
Work.
Work. Okay.

04:31.080 --> 04:32.115
Stools?

04:32.120 --> 04:34.281
Yes.

04:34.290 --> 04:36.702
[ Metal scraping ]

04:36.710 --> 04:38.610
[ Metal thuds ]

04:42.710 --> 04:44.166
[ Grunts ]

04:44.960 --> 04:47.702
In case _
I neglected to mentIon,

04:47.710 --> 04:48.950
it's good to see you.

04:48.960 --> 04:50.996
I mean, you could have
called first.

04:51.000 --> 04:52.240
[ Chuckles ]
Next time.

04:52.250 --> 04:53.956
Oh, there's not gonna be
a next time.

04:53.960 --> 04:55.370
That's what I'm saying.

04:55.380 --> 04:57.325
As soon as I crack this safe,
I'm done.

04:57.330 --> 04:58.536
Fair enough.

04:58.540 --> 05:00.201
Though,
I do find it strange

05:00.210 --> 05:02.417
you're about
to break into a vault

05:02.420 --> 05:04.115
and you don't even ask
what's in it.

05:04.120 --> 05:05.326
'Cause I don't care
what's in it.

05:05.330 --> 05:06.615
I do.

05:06.620 --> 05:09.783
That's why I only hire
the best guys for the job.

05:09.790 --> 05:12.202
That is every single toy
you asked for.

05:12.210 --> 05:13.950
[ Dialing ]

05:13.960 --> 05:15.666
[ Cellphone beeps ]

05:17.330 --> 05:20.572
[ Line ringing ]

05:20.580 --> 05:21.660
[ Click ]

05:21.670 --> 05:23.035
So far, so good with us.

05:23.040 --> 05:24.200
You?

05:24.210 --> 05:27.111
Yeah. I'm here.

05:27.120 --> 05:29.702
Grey gives you any trouble,
just let me know.

05:29.710 --> 05:31.450
Alright.

05:31.460 --> 05:33.951
Sharkey, can you put that
wherever you're supposed to?

05:33.960 --> 05:34.699
Sharkey: Yep. Got it.

05:34.710 --> 05:36.450
Hello.
Hey.

05:36.460 --> 05:37.666
Can I get you something?

05:37.670 --> 05:39.069
Yeah.

05:39.080 --> 05:40.536
I've got some time
to kill.

05:40.540 --> 05:43.532
Mm. Spicy Bloody,
extra horseradish, three olives.

05:45.500 --> 05:47.115
Yep. Coming right up.

05:47.120 --> 05:48.701
Thanks.

05:50.580 --> 05:52.161
[ Pen clicks ]

06:02.380 --> 06:03.699
Darius: I think he knows.

06:03.710 --> 06:04.995
Hoffman:
We would have heard something

06:05.000 --> 06:06.570
if Kane was suspicious.

06:06.580 --> 06:07.740
I'm scared.

06:07.750 --> 06:09.069
I'm scared.

06:09.080 --> 06:10.707
Darius,
shake that off, man.

06:10.710 --> 06:12.701
[ Knock on door ]

06:12.710 --> 06:15.031
[ Siren walls in distance ]

06:16.250 --> 06:17.239
Detective Lee: Here.

06:17.250 --> 06:18.956
I appreciate this.

06:18.960 --> 06:20.746
Cosgrove finds out

06:20.750 --> 06:22.536
you are not in Hawaii
and that I knew,

06:22.540 --> 06:23.825
I could lose my job.

06:23.830 --> 06:25.991
Your secret's
safe with me.
Yeah.

06:26.000 --> 06:27.240
What's the latest
on Kane?

06:27.250 --> 06:29.571
[ Sighs ] Marshals are convinced
that he's in Canada.

06:29.580 --> 06:32.743
They're coordinating efforts
with the CSIS and the RCMP.

06:32.750 --> 06:34.320
That doesn't add up.
I know.

06:34.330 --> 06:36.457
He has no money,
no resources.

06:36.460 --> 06:38.872
All of his connections
are here in Portland.

06:38.880 --> 06:40.324
[ Sighs ]
What about McConnell?

06:40.330 --> 06:41.661
Yeah,
he wasn't at the bar.

06:41.670 --> 06:43.206
Some lady
was running the place.

06:43.210 --> 06:44.370
I've seen her
at the station.

06:44.380 --> 06:45.824
Dax?
Dex?

06:45.830 --> 06:47.786
Yeah.
Did you talk to her?

06:47.790 --> 06:49.951
I got my own work to do,
Miles.

06:49.960 --> 06:51.996
I'm not even
supposed to be here.

06:52.000 --> 06:54.207
Neither are you.

06:58.420 --> 06:59.990
[ Line rings ]

07:00.000 --> 07:01.240
[ Cellphone beeps ]

07:01.250 --> 07:02.319
Grey never
turns his phone off.

07:02.330 --> 07:03.376
Something's up.

07:03.380 --> 07:04.779
It's from Edgar.

07:04.790 --> 07:05.996
Who's Edgar?
The chef.

07:06.000 --> 07:08.207
He quit?
He quit.

07:08.210 --> 07:09.746
Okay.
Well, it's burgers and fries.

07:09.750 --> 07:11.240
How hard can that be,
right?

07:11.250 --> 07:13.741
I just wanna
treat you better

07:13.750 --> 07:15.160
We need a new chef.

07:15.170 --> 07:17.411
Woman: [ Singing in Spanish ]

07:17.420 --> 07:19.206
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Yo, check it out.

07:19.210 --> 07:20.996
C.J. McCollum
from the Blazers --

07:21.000 --> 07:22.376
I know who he is, dummy.

07:22.380 --> 07:24.075
He just liked us
on Insta.

07:24.080 --> 07:25.069
Seriously?

07:25.080 --> 07:26.616
Yeah.
You know what I heard?

07:26.620 --> 07:27.826
The food critic
from The Outlook --

07:27.830 --> 07:28.785
I guess
that's a newspaper?

07:28.790 --> 07:30.417
Yes, it's a newspaper.

07:30.420 --> 07:31.990
What about him?
I heard he might be
sniffing around here,

07:32.000 --> 07:33.160
looking to do a review.

07:33.170 --> 07:35.206
You're blowing up, dude.
[ Chuckles ]

07:35.210 --> 07:36.666
I've outgrown this place.

07:36.670 --> 07:38.376
Don't say it.
I'm saying it.

07:38.380 --> 07:40.280
How can I spread my wings

07:40.290 --> 07:42.326
when I can barely fit
inside this fishbowl?

07:42.330 --> 07:44.321
[ Inhales sharply ]

07:44.330 --> 07:46.070
That's two things,
but you get my meaning.

07:46.080 --> 07:48.036
[ Cellphone vibrates, rings ]

07:50.420 --> 07:51.876
What's up, Dex?

07:51.880 --> 07:54.166
Man:
[ Rapping in Spanish ]

07:59.790 --> 08:01.417
[ Exhales sharply]

08:01.420 --> 08:03.115
Oh, Took.

08:03.120 --> 08:05.031
Oh. Bless you.
Tookie: [Chuckles]

08:05.040 --> 08:07.110
What is all this?

08:07.120 --> 08:08.781
Welcome
to the magIc show.

08:08.790 --> 08:11.111
That doesn't
answer anything.

08:11.120 --> 08:13.247
These are the ingredients
that are gonna take me

08:13.250 --> 08:16.822
from a taco truck _
to my own restaurant [SnIffs]

08:16.830 --> 08:18.878
to the cover
of Food & Wine mag.

08:18.880 --> 08:20.529
Okay. That's great.

08:20.540 --> 08:21.916
I just -- You know, I need you
to grill the burgers

08:21.920 --> 08:22.955
and fry the fries.

08:22.960 --> 08:24.416
Mm. No can do.
Word is out.

08:24.420 --> 08:26.957
Tonight at the Bad Alibi
is my pop-up debut --

08:26.960 --> 08:29.326
elevated Mexican cuisine.

08:29.330 --> 08:31.878
I'm gonna show the world that
I'm about more than just tacos.

08:31.880 --> 08:33.165
Yeah. It'sjust, um...
Come on.

08:33.170 --> 08:34.956
Let's scratch
each other's itch.

08:34.960 --> 08:37.497
Oh, God, you have an ability
to make anything sound gross.

08:37.500 --> 08:39.411
[ Chuckles ]

08:39.420 --> 08:44.699
[ Metal grinding ]

08:44.710 --> 08:46.325
Two hours, man.

08:46.330 --> 08:47.490
You're not even
through the lock.

08:47.500 --> 08:50.458
Steel plates,
reinforced concrete.

08:50.460 --> 08:51.870
Which means?

08:51.880 --> 08:54.166
It's cross your fingers
I'll be done in four hours.

08:56.290 --> 08:57.416
Can you just blow
the damn thing?

08:57.420 --> 08:58.455
[ Grinding stops ]

08:58.460 --> 09:00.451
Look, if the charges
aren't set right,

09:00.460 --> 09:01.825
they're gonna be cleaning
our bodies off the floor

09:01.830 --> 09:02.819
with a squeegee.

09:02.830 --> 09:04.570
You understand?

09:04.580 --> 09:05.990
I mean, how many of these
have we done together, man?

09:06.000 --> 09:07.706
Five? Six?

09:07.710 --> 09:09.325
Since when did you get
the shakes?

09:10.880 --> 09:11.824
When I had a kid.

09:13.460 --> 09:14.449
You had a kid?

09:14.460 --> 09:16.416
A girl. Kami.

09:16.420 --> 09:17.739
6 months.
[ Laughs ]

09:17.750 --> 09:19.536
Wow, man. Congrats.

09:19.540 --> 09:20.780
That's -- Hey, man,
it's a big responsibility.

09:20.790 --> 09:22.280
Good on you.
Yeah.

09:22.290 --> 09:24.201
Makes you rethink stuff,
you know?

09:24.210 --> 09:26.917
So don't screw up.
[ Chuckles ]

09:26.920 --> 09:27.989
Alright, man.

09:28.000 --> 09:31.822
[ Grinding resumes ]

09:31.830 --> 09:33.741
Alright. Here you are.

09:33.750 --> 09:35.115
It's interesting.

09:35.120 --> 09:36.371
Never had
a Bloody Mary with --

09:36.380 --> 09:38.280
What is that,
pineapple juice?

09:38.290 --> 09:39.917
It's a work in progress.
Aren't we all?

09:39.920 --> 09:42.036
[ Chuckles nervously ]

09:42.040 --> 09:42.950
Hey,
what are you having?

09:42.960 --> 09:44.370
If it's, uh,
beer or wine,

09:45.710 --> 09:47.280
I'm looking for
Dex Parios?

09:47.290 --> 09:49.030
[Tap sputters ]
Sorr-- Uh, yes, that's me.

09:49.040 --> 09:51.998
I'm Janet Withers,
DPSST.

09:52.000 --> 09:54.036
I'm here for your
certification interview.

09:54.040 --> 09:55.496
Yes. Hi. Sorry.
Nice to meet you.

09:55.500 --> 09:56.569
Thanks for coming down.

09:56.580 --> 09:58.957
Um, why don't we grab
a seat over there?

09:58.960 --> 10:00.200
Okay.
Great.

10:00.210 --> 10:00.949
Can I get a water,
please?

10:00.960 --> 10:03.201
Yeah, absolutely. Um...

10:03.210 --> 10:05.371
[Tap hissing ]
Okay. Come on.

10:05.380 --> 10:06.995
Buddy, you got
to take over, okay?

10:07.000 --> 10:08.115
It's not working.
It's not coming out.

10:08.120 --> 10:10.202
It's. ..
[Tap sputters ]

10:10.210 --> 10:12.576
You did your apprentice hours
under Arthur Banks?

10:12.580 --> 10:13.786
Yes. Yep.

10:13.790 --> 10:15.496
What would you say

10:15.500 --> 10:18.116
are the top three things
you learned from Arthur?

10:18.120 --> 10:19.166
Honon

10:19.170 --> 10:20.159
Mm-hmm.

10:20.170 --> 10:21.376
Uh...

10:21.380 --> 10:22.495
integrity.

10:22.500 --> 10:23.205
Mm.

10:25.380 --> 10:27.325
Those are really the two
that we just focused on.

10:27.330 --> 10:29.378
Uh, could Ijust
leave it at two?

10:29.380 --> 10:30.824
Sure.

10:30.830 --> 10:32.616
Do you engage
in recreational drug use?

10:32.620 --> 10:33.609
No, ma'am.

10:33.620 --> 10:34.780
Alcohol?

10:34.790 --> 10:36.610
Uh, in moderation.

10:36.620 --> 10:38.247
[ Chuckles ]

10:38.250 --> 10:39.569
I-Is that wrong or --

10:39.580 --> 10:40.820
No, no, no, no, no.

10:40.830 --> 10:43.458
I like a Midori sour
as much as the next sailor.

10:43.460 --> 10:44.609
[ Chuckles ]
Just not on the job.

10:44.620 --> 10:46.372
Of course.

10:46.380 --> 10:48.166
Have you ever been convicted
of a felony?
No.

10:48.170 --> 10:49.410
Do you associate
with anyone

10:49.420 --> 10:50.569
who's been convicted
of a felony?

10:50.580 --> 10:52.491
No.

10:52.500 --> 10:54.070
Why do you want to be
a private investigator?

10:54.080 --> 10:55.877
What?

10:55.880 --> 10:57.324
It's a simple question.

10:57.330 --> 10:58.661
Surely you've thought
about it.

10:58.670 --> 11:00.319
Yeah.
Of -- Of course I have.

11:00.330 --> 11:02.707
Um, uh, deeply,
I've considered it.

11:02.710 --> 11:06.077
Um...I just, uh --

11:06.080 --> 11:07.411
I really like
helping people?

11:07.420 --> 11:09.320
Is that a question?
Um --

11:09.330 --> 11:11.070
'Cause when
you're parked outside

11:11.080 --> 11:12.911
a cheap motel
on the interstate

11:12.920 --> 11:15.741
six hours into
an all-nIght stakeout,

11:15.750 --> 11:18.287
your bladder's about to explode,
your pee bottle's full,

11:18.290 --> 11:20.110
and you're fresh out of
adult diapers,

11:20.120 --> 11:22.031
your car smells like
the five-day-old chalupa

11:22.040 --> 11:23.780
you lost under your seat,

11:23.790 --> 11:25.166
your last client
stiffed you,

11:25.170 --> 11:27.320
and you don't know where
the next one's coming from,

11:27.330 --> 11:29.070
I can assure you,
you will be asking yourself

11:29.080 --> 11:31.537
the same question --
"Why the hell

11:31.540 --> 11:34.703
would I_want_to be
a prIvate InvestIgator?"

11:34.710 --> 11:37.497
[ Chuckles nervously ]

11:37.500 --> 11:39.286
Uh...

11:39.290 --> 11:40.496
I know I'm supposed
to have a good answer,

11:40.500 --> 11:41.910
but I don't.

11:41.920 --> 11:43.740
Um...

11:43.750 --> 11:46.742
The truth is, I, um --

11:46.750 --> 11:48.377
I drink a little _bit too much
sometImes.

11:48.380 --> 11:51.417
Um, my best friend
is a felon,

11:51.420 --> 11:54.207
and I haven't been able
to hold down a real job

11:54.210 --> 11:56.166
in about 10 years.

11:56.170 --> 11:58.536
But this?

11:58.540 --> 11:59.700
This, I'm -- I'm good at.

11:59.710 --> 12:02.247
I-I-I don't know why,
but I -- but I am.

12:02.250 --> 12:04.241
And you seem pretty cynical
about the whole thing,

12:04.250 --> 12:05.490
and maybe one day,
I will be, too,

12:05.500 --> 12:07.070
but, um [Sighs]

12:07.080 --> 12:08.490
from where I'm sitting
right now,

12:08.500 --> 12:10.070
that chalupa is smelling
pretty damn good.

12:10.080 --> 12:11.456
[ Rock music playing ]

12:11.460 --> 12:13.200
Let's turn the lights down

12:13.210 --> 12:14.996
Yeah. Wrong answer.

12:15.000 --> 12:16.956
[ Clears throat ]

12:16.960 --> 12:18.609
It was honest.

12:18.620 --> 12:19.996
Oh, oh-oh

12:20.000 --> 12:21.206
Let's turn the lights down

12:21.210 --> 12:23.110
I have
everything I need.

12:23.120 --> 12:24.610
And we'll have
an answer soon.

12:24.620 --> 12:26.827
So, thank you
for your time.

12:26.830 --> 12:28.991
Thank you
for coming down.

12:30.620 --> 12:33.578
[ Sighs ] Oh, my God.

12:33.580 --> 12:35.377
[ Cellphone ringing ]

12:37.880 --> 12:38.915
[ Cellphone beeps ]

12:38.920 --> 12:39.955
Cosgrove: Miles.

12:39.960 --> 12:41.029
Oh, hey, Lieutenant.

12:41.040 --> 12:42.200
How's Hawaii?

12:42.210 --> 12:43.575
Yeah, no, Ijust got in.

12:43.580 --> 12:45.957
It's, um --
It's something else.

12:45.960 --> 12:48.326
Yeah, it's, uh -- Wow.

12:48.330 --> 12:50.491
I c-- I know it sounds clich,

12:50.500 --> 12:53.242
but, uh, yeah,
this place is paradise.

12:53.250 --> 12:54.786
[ Knock on door ]
You really deserve
this trip, Miles.

12:54.790 --> 12:56.109
Yeah, no.

12:56.120 --> 12:58.372
Uh, look, if I could,
I'd, uh --

12:58.380 --> 12:59.824
I really wish
I could show you this view.

12:59.830 --> 13:01.786
It's, uh -- Whew.

13:01.790 --> 13:05.829
Maybe I'll take a picture
and send it to you 'cause it --

13:05.830 --> 13:07.707
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Damn it.

13:07.710 --> 13:08.870
Aloha.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

13:08.880 --> 13:11.701
Lieutenant.

13:11.710 --> 13:13.075
Did I think __
you were gonna go to HawaII?

13:13.080 --> 13:14.286
No.

13:14.290 --> 13:15.370
What I did believe

13:15.380 --> 13:16.699
is that you'd have
enough faith in me

13:16.710 --> 13:18.450
to know that
I was lookIng out for you.

13:18.460 --> 13:19.870
Let me put this guy
back in prison.

13:19.880 --> 13:21.029
Are you listening
to what I'm saying?

13:21.040 --> 13:22.166
Did you just come here
to scold me?

13:22.170 --> 13:23.706
No.
I came to take your badge.

13:23.710 --> 13:25.610
Are you serious?
You've been digging around.

13:25.620 --> 13:26.826
The brass found out.

13:26.830 --> 13:27.956
I told you.

13:27.960 --> 13:30.246
I answer to people, too.

13:30.250 --> 13:31.820
So I'm supposed to just
walk away?

13:36.000 --> 13:38.070
You're under review, Miles.

13:38.080 --> 13:40.662
Your badge is on the line.

13:40.670 --> 13:43.707
You go anywhere near this case,
and you could lose it.

13:46.580 --> 13:48.571
[ Mid-tempo music playing ]
[ Sniffs ]

13:48.580 --> 13:50.741
Adobo.

13:50.750 --> 13:52.661
Vinegar.
Man: Hey.
You see who that is?

13:52.670 --> 13:53.785
The acid is on point.

13:53.790 --> 13:55.530
I'm impressed.

13:55.540 --> 13:57.280
I'm not just
a basketball player.
I know.

13:57.290 --> 13:59.667
C.J. McCollum --
king of the mid-range,

13:59.670 --> 14:01.740
also the host of
the "Pull Up" podcast.

14:01.750 --> 14:04.321
I'm a fan.
That's love.
I appreCIate that.

14:04.330 --> 14:06.286
But I love food as much
as I love hooping.

14:07.710 --> 14:09.780
[ Crunching ]

14:11.960 --> 14:14.747
Is this venison?

14:14.750 --> 14:16.115
Goat. The cheek.

14:16.120 --> 14:17.246
It's the most tender cut.

14:17.250 --> 14:19.411
There's something unusual
in here.

14:19.420 --> 14:21.536
Braised in beer
from a local brewery.

14:21.540 --> 14:23.531
This is a cold-blooded dagger
off the pick-and-roll.

14:23.540 --> 14:24.609
[ Chuckles ]
Respect, bro.

14:24.620 --> 14:26.201
I, sir, am humbled.

14:26.210 --> 14:29.327
You mind ifI out this
on the 'Gram?

14:29.330 --> 14:30.615
Gotta get Dame
to come through, too.

14:30.620 --> 14:32.281
Yeah.
And tag me on Insta.

14:32.290 --> 14:33.166
I need the likes.
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

14:33.170 --> 14:34.706
I got you.

14:37.000 --> 14:39.377
Denton: Hey, listen.

14:39.380 --> 14:41.450
I want my cut
before we leave this place.

14:41.460 --> 14:44.418
That was the deal.

14:44.420 --> 14:45.910
And I'm a man of my word.

14:49.080 --> 14:51.708
[ Exhales deeply ]

14:51.710 --> 14:53.610
[ Groans ]

14:55.420 --> 14:56.455
[ Tools thud ]

14:56.460 --> 14:59.372
When Denton's done,
he's done.

14:59.380 --> 15:01.166
I'll need help
with disposal.

15:01.170 --> 15:03.786
No.
I'm not killing anyone.

15:03.790 --> 15:05.166
Hey.

15:07.000 --> 15:09.412
The reason I don't give him
his cut up front

15:09.420 --> 15:12.162
is because you and Feeney
blew the money.

15:12.170 --> 15:14.661
So you'll do what I ask
when I ask it.

15:14.670 --> 15:18.379
Or I'll have to take something
very clear from you.

15:21.580 --> 15:23.821
[ Groans ]

15:23.830 --> 15:26.162
I've got to have it

15:26.170 --> 15:27.819
Hey, buddy,
what do you think?

15:27.830 --> 15:30.913
Five letters --
young oak.

15:32.000 --> 15:33.786
"Acorn"?

15:34.880 --> 15:36.609
Nice.

15:38.540 --> 15:39.871
Hi.

15:39.880 --> 15:41.416
Hey.

15:41.420 --> 15:42.660
How's it going?

15:42.670 --> 15:43.955
[ Exhales sharply]
Pretty rough.

15:43.960 --> 15:47.168
I just had my P.I. certification
interview,

15:47.170 --> 15:49.456
and I blew it.

15:49.460 --> 15:50.449
Oh, don't sweat it.

15:50.460 --> 15:52.166
I got a job for you.

15:52.170 --> 15:53.660
It's a missing-persons case.

15:53.670 --> 15:55.069
He's in the wind,
and I need to find him.

15:55.080 --> 15:56.741
VVho?

15:56.750 --> 15:58.615
Grey.

16:04.750 --> 16:06.615
[ Exhales heavily ]
Are you serious?

16:06.620 --> 16:08.110
Completely.

16:08.120 --> 16:10.873
That bald dude --

16:10.880 --> 16:12.370
I'm pretty sure
he's the guy,

16:12.380 --> 16:13.870
the Outlook
restaurant crItIc.

16:13.880 --> 16:16.667
I need you
tending bar.

16:16.670 --> 16:18.285
Okay.

16:18.290 --> 16:20.281
Okay, let me, uh,
get this clear.

16:20.290 --> 16:22.497
You want me to spy
on my best friend?

16:22.500 --> 16:23.740
No, not spy.

16:23.750 --> 16:25.286
I just want you to help me
find out where he is.

16:25.290 --> 16:26.609
Okay.
Well, that's easy.

16:26.620 --> 16:27.826
[Taps table ]

16:27.830 --> 16:29.661
[ Glasses clinking ]

16:29.670 --> 16:30.614
Hey, Ansel.

16:30.620 --> 16:32.497
Where's Grey?

16:32.500 --> 16:34.070
Visiting his sick aunt
in Houston.

16:34.080 --> 16:36.571
There you go.
Yes. Case closed.

16:36.580 --> 16:38.320
You owe me $500.

16:38.330 --> 16:40.207
Uh, do you really think
he went to Houston?

16:40.210 --> 16:41.575
Can I show you something
real quick?

16:41.580 --> 16:42.706
What is it?

16:42.710 --> 16:43.779
Uh, the door.

16:43.790 --> 16:45.530
Get out.

16:46.250 --> 16:48.821
[ Sighs ]
Give me 20 minutes
back at my apartment.

16:48.830 --> 16:50.491
Please. I'm serious.

16:50.500 --> 16:51.819
If you care about Grey,

16:51.830 --> 16:54.242
you're gonna wanna see
what I have to show you.

16:56.080 --> 17:00.198
Kane protected Grey
and Jack Feeney in prison.

17:00.210 --> 17:03.111
Word from inside is that
both Grey and Feeney

17:03.120 --> 17:04.701
owed Kane
for that protection.

17:04.710 --> 17:06.666
Feeney ends up dead.

17:06.670 --> 17:08.376
Two days later,
Kane escapes.

17:08.380 --> 17:10.280
Now, I strongly believe

17:10.290 --> 17:13.498
that Grey is with Kane
right now on a job.

17:15.500 --> 17:16.876
[ Sighs ]

17:16.880 --> 17:18.529
So you want me to help find Grey
so you can arrest him?

17:18.540 --> 17:21.703
I don't care about Grey.
I want Kane.

17:21.710 --> 17:26.409
I told you that he killed
one of my C.I.s 10 years ago.

17:26.420 --> 17:29.992
He had a wife
and a one-month-old baby.

17:34.040 --> 17:37.874
You have to find Grey.
Now.

17:44.880 --> 17:48.202
Don't make me
put that back up, please.

17:48.210 --> 17:49.370
Okay.

17:49.380 --> 17:55.819
Oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, ohh-oh

17:55.830 --> 17:57.878
Tell him this is
a churro taco souffl

17:57.880 --> 18:02.283
with cajeta tapioca cream
and piloncillo syrup.

18:02.290 --> 18:03.746
Churro. Got it.

18:03.750 --> 18:06.412
And finally a soupon,
as they say in culinary circles,

18:06.420 --> 18:08.376
of my special magic sauce.

18:08.380 --> 18:10.996
Now, you wanna wait
until he takes a bite

18:11.000 --> 18:12.115
to make sure
he's all good.

18:12.120 --> 18:13.496
But don't let on

18:13.500 --> 18:15.570
that you know
he's a food critic.

18:15.580 --> 18:18.879
If he knows we know
that he knows we know,

18:18.880 --> 18:20.074
he won't review us.

18:20.080 --> 18:21.206
Give me the plate.

18:21.210 --> 18:23.075
Wait -- Go.

18:23.080 --> 18:26.959
Ohhh

18:26.960 --> 18:30.919
Oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, ohh-oh

18:30.920 --> 18:32.490
Just like that

18:32.500 --> 18:36.072
Oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, ohh-oh

18:36.080 --> 18:37.456
Ohh, oh-oh

18:37.460 --> 18:39.701
When I smile to disguise...

18:39.710 --> 18:41.325
That looks good.

18:41.330 --> 18:42.877
Thanks, buddy.

18:42.880 --> 18:45.610
Hey, real quick, kid.

18:45.620 --> 18:48.202
Five letters --
Bert's bud.

18:48.210 --> 18:49.370
Ernie.

18:49.380 --> 18:50.529
You're good.

18:50.540 --> 18:52.110
You like it?

18:52.120 --> 18:53.826
Love it.

18:53.830 --> 18:56.071
Say, you're friends
with Grey, right?

18:59.330 --> 19:02.163
This tug of war
within my soul

19:02.170 --> 19:03.114
Although silent

19:05.960 --> 19:08.497
This will initiate
the reaction.

19:08.500 --> 19:11.116
And then we're gonna need
15 feet of clearance for safety.

19:11.120 --> 19:12.576
You're the expert.

19:12.580 --> 19:15.993
And, look,
about, uh, Denton --

19:16.000 --> 19:17.206
let me talk to him, okay?

19:17.210 --> 19:18.746
I'm sure he's just
a little on edge,

19:18.750 --> 19:19.956
like everybody else,

19:19.960 --> 19:22.372
but you don't have
to take him out.

19:22.380 --> 19:24.109
Alright.

19:24.120 --> 19:25.496
I appreciate it.

19:33.000 --> 19:35.912
[ Click]
[ Dialing ]

19:35.920 --> 19:38.571
[ Line ringing ]

19:38.580 --> 19:40.116
[ Cellphone vibrates, beeps ]

19:40.120 --> 19:41.701
Hey.
Kane: Looks like
we're gonna need

19:41.710 --> 19:42.950
a little insurance.
Mm-hmm.

19:42.960 --> 19:44.825
We need to make sure
Grey cooperates.

19:44.830 --> 19:47.879
Yeah.
I'll take care of it.

19:47.880 --> 19:53.739
[ Mid-tempo music playing ]

19:53.750 --> 19:54.990
[ Crunch ]

19:55.000 --> 19:56.570
[ Sighs ]
This feels weird,

19:56.580 --> 19:58.571
snooping around
in Grey's office with you.

19:58.580 --> 20:00.241
I'm just a client.

20:00.250 --> 20:02.571
Well, I wouldn't
bring my client on a job.

20:02.580 --> 20:04.491
Except this client
just happens to be a cop.

20:04.500 --> 20:06.161
Yeah. Who I've also
hooked up with.
Your point being?

20:06.170 --> 20:07.410
That it feels weird

20:07.420 --> 20:09.456
snooping around
in Grey's office with you.

20:09.460 --> 20:11.109
Okay, look,
you want to protect him.

20:11.120 --> 20:12.576
That's sweet.

20:12.580 --> 20:14.116
Do you know the combination
to this thing?

20:14.120 --> 20:15.826
No, not a clue.

20:15.830 --> 20:17.115
Okay, well,
it's usually the birth date

20:17.120 --> 20:18.246
of somebody
you care about.

20:18.250 --> 20:19.820
You want to humor me,
try yours?

20:19.830 --> 20:22.162
[ Sighs ]
Come on.

20:22.170 --> 20:23.990
Come on.

20:24.000 --> 20:24.955
[ Sighs ]

20:26.960 --> 20:28.996
[ Dial clicking ]

20:31.620 --> 20:33.997
[ Safe door opens ]

20:34.000 --> 20:35.570
Adorable.

20:35.580 --> 20:36.820
I tried my brother's.

20:36.830 --> 20:38.377
[ Clears throat ]

20:40.000 --> 20:41.319
He owns a bar.

20:41.330 --> 20:43.116
I mean, it's --
it's practically insurance.

20:43.120 --> 20:44.496
Grey is
a convicted felon.

20:44.500 --> 20:46.286
It's illegal for him
to own a gun.

20:46.290 --> 20:47.951
Well, it's a good thing
we only found bullets.

20:47.960 --> 20:50.030
Which tells me that he probably
has the gun on him,

20:50.040 --> 20:51.496
and if he has the gun
on him...

20:51.500 --> 20:53.286
He wouldn't be able
to get on a plane

20:53.290 --> 20:54.450
and go to Houston.

20:54.460 --> 20:55.700
There you go.

20:55.710 --> 20:57.200
[ Sighs ]

20:58.620 --> 21:00.076
What's all this?

21:03.380 --> 21:05.325
Grey's an explosives
expert.

21:05.330 --> 21:06.536
You didn't know that?

21:06.540 --> 21:07.916
What?

21:07.920 --> 21:11.492
N-No, Grey went to prison
for grand theft.

21:11.500 --> 21:13.661
Among other things,
yeah.

21:13.670 --> 21:15.456
Hoffman: 312 Customs.

21:15.460 --> 21:17.280
You got to be kidding me.

21:17.290 --> 21:18.700
Ex-con named Petey
runs it.

21:18.710 --> 21:21.167
He's got a really long
rap sheet.

21:22.250 --> 21:24.571
[ Sighs ]

21:24.580 --> 21:25.615
Denton: What's that?

21:25.620 --> 21:27.497
I could use some quiet time.

21:27.500 --> 21:29.115
If I'm risking my neck,
I want to know what's going on.

21:29.120 --> 21:32.374
Alright,
this is C-4, okay?

21:32.380 --> 21:34.075
And explosives
are like dogs.

21:34.080 --> 21:36.321
They need to be told what to do
so they know how to please.

21:36.330 --> 21:38.992
I just need enough
to blow open this door

21:39.000 --> 21:41.036
so I can keep
what's inside safe.

21:43.120 --> 21:45.372
Hey, Denton,
do me a favor.

21:45.380 --> 21:46.529
Okay.

21:46.540 --> 21:49.031
Just quit running your mouth
around Kane.

21:49.040 --> 21:50.530
You know something
I don't?

21:50.540 --> 21:52.997
You heard what I said,
okay?

21:53.000 --> 21:55.537
Just do your job,
yeah?

22:02.080 --> 22:05.959
Tookie, man,
we're out of cilantro.

22:05.960 --> 22:08.201
_ That's a disaster.
DInner's gonna be a mob scene.

22:11.250 --> 22:13.161
I need you to make
a cilantro run.

22:13.170 --> 22:15.115
Can you handle that?
Yes.

22:15.120 --> 22:17.873
Go to Shemanski Market
on West Huber Street.

22:17.880 --> 22:19.416
Buy up all the cilantro
they have left.
Okay.

22:19.420 --> 22:20.455
Hurry.
Okay.

22:26.790 --> 22:27.870
[ Window clicks, whirs ]

22:27.880 --> 22:28.995
Frank: Hey, pal.

22:29.000 --> 22:30.240
Grey called.

22:30.250 --> 22:32.070
He wants me
to take you to him.

22:32.080 --> 22:33.741
He's in Houston.
Nope.

22:33.750 --> 22:35.206
He's here.

22:35.210 --> 22:37.531
He's planning a surprise party
for your sister.

22:37.540 --> 22:40.031
I'm not supposed to get
in strangers' cars.

22:40.040 --> 22:43.498
I'm not a stranger.
I'm Grey's friend, like you.

22:43.500 --> 22:46.742
Guess that makes us friends,
too, doesn't it?

22:49.210 --> 22:50.666
[ Laughing ]
Come on. Let's go.

22:58.670 --> 22:59.739
You want a shot?

22:59.750 --> 23:00.990
No. You okay?

23:01.000 --> 23:03.207
Hey, Tookie,
where's Ansel?

23:03.210 --> 23:05.917
Cilantro run.
He'll be back in five.
Alright.

23:05.920 --> 23:08.411
Look, I know
how hard this can be,

23:08.420 --> 23:09.785
finding out
that somebody you trusted

23:09.790 --> 23:10.950
isn't who you thought
they were.

23:10.960 --> 23:13.110
No. I know Grey, okay?

23:13.120 --> 23:14.747
He must have gotten
mixed up in something.

23:14.750 --> 23:15.660
[ Glass thuds ]

23:15.670 --> 23:18.036
[ Sighing ]

23:18.040 --> 23:19.530
I'm gonna go
check out 312.

23:19.540 --> 23:21.371
I'll take a look around
Grey's loft.

23:21.380 --> 23:22.574
Alright.
If you find anything, just --

23:22.580 --> 23:23.535
Yes, I will call you.

23:24.670 --> 23:26.456
I promise.

23:26.460 --> 23:30.373
...to wait at all

23:30.380 --> 23:32.029
All you said...

23:32.040 --> 23:36.488
I've never read

23:36.500 --> 23:37.569
[ Sighs ]

23:37.580 --> 23:38.706
[ Cash register beeps ]

23:38.710 --> 23:40.280
Where's Grey?

23:40.290 --> 23:43.248
Oh, I'm sorry, buddy.
He's stuck in traffic.

23:43.250 --> 23:45.070
Hey, do you like
ice cream sundaes?

23:45.080 --> 23:47.116
'Cause this place
makes the best.

23:47.120 --> 23:49.076
Let's grab a booth.
Come on.

23:49.080 --> 23:50.877
[ Indistinct conversations ]

23:50.880 --> 23:52.199
This one's great.

23:52.210 --> 23:54.952
...you read in school

23:54.960 --> 23:55.949
Alright.

23:55.960 --> 23:58.167
Oh, real quick.

23:58.170 --> 23:59.876
[ Beep]
Say, "Hi, Grey."

23:59.880 --> 24:01.575
Hi, Grey.

24:01.580 --> 24:02.535
Perfect.

24:02.540 --> 24:03.871
[ Cellphone beeps, clicks ]

24:03.880 --> 24:06.451
Now, don't get yourself
into a lather, Greyson.

24:06.460 --> 24:07.825
Frank's just gonna
sit there with him

24:07.830 --> 24:10.742
until he hears back
from me.

24:10.750 --> 24:11.876
Whatever you need, Kane.

24:12.880 --> 24:15.326
Well,
that's what I figured.

24:15.330 --> 24:17.286
Go make us rich.

24:20.670 --> 24:22.285
[ Sighs ]

