30:40.620 --> 30:41.609
Just what I needed

30:41.620 --> 30:42.996
[ Groaning ]
[ Panting ]

30:43.000 --> 30:45.286
I needed someone to bleed

30:47.460 --> 30:50.031
[ Door squeaks ]

30:50.040 --> 30:51.246
[ Gasps ]

30:51.250 --> 30:52.660
Hey, don't freak out.

30:52.670 --> 30:54.240
Uh...
Okay?

30:54.250 --> 30:59.119
[ Breathing heavily ]

30:59.120 --> 31:01.497
Take this, okay?
Keep everybody out of here.

31:01.500 --> 31:02.535
For how long?

31:02.540 --> 31:03.780
Give me five minutes.

31:03.790 --> 31:04.996
Eight, tops.

31:06.830 --> 31:08.707
[ Exhales sharply]
Okay.

31:08.710 --> 31:09.916
[ Keypad beeps ]

31:09.920 --> 31:11.615
Get ready.

31:11.620 --> 31:12.871
What's happening?

31:12.880 --> 31:13.869
The safe's
about to explode.

31:13.880 --> 31:15.074
Oh, man. Hold on.

31:16.670 --> 31:18.114
[ Exhales sharply]
Okay.

31:23.580 --> 31:24.569
Alright, here we go.

31:24.580 --> 31:26.320
Three, two...

31:26.330 --> 31:28.662
[ Detonator beeps,
explosive pops ]

31:28.670 --> 31:29.785
That's it?

31:29.790 --> 31:30.996
That's it.

31:33.710 --> 31:35.029
Hoffman: Dex!

31:35.040 --> 31:36.951
Dex: Yeah. Here.
Hey.

31:36.960 --> 31:37.699
Where's your brother?

31:37.710 --> 31:39.200
He's -- He's okay.

31:39.210 --> 31:40.825
Listen, this guy didn't know
where the job was,

31:40.830 --> 31:42.878
but he did say that Kane
had him set up a fence

31:42.880 --> 31:44.871
that sells
Native American artifacts.

31:44.880 --> 31:46.416
What -- What did you get
from Petey?

31:46.420 --> 31:48.411
He said Kane bought enough
explosives to blow a vault.

31:48.420 --> 31:49.614
Okay. What vault?

31:51.250 --> 31:53.036
Artifacts.

31:55.250 --> 31:57.070
Portland Museum.

31:57.080 --> 31:58.456
Worth a try.

31:58.460 --> 31:59.825
Listen, I need to take
my brother home, okay?

31:59.830 --> 32:00.876
Can you deal with this?

32:00.880 --> 32:01.915
[ Door opens ]

32:01.920 --> 32:03.911
I-I'll call it in.

32:15.540 --> 32:17.326
Denton:
All this for a rock?

32:17.330 --> 32:19.207
Oh, this is
no ordinary rock.

32:19.210 --> 32:23.704
This obsidian ax
is 12,000 years old.

32:23.710 --> 32:25.109
What's it worth?

32:25.120 --> 32:27.702
When something is this rare
and this valuable,

32:27.710 --> 32:29.996
they call it priceless.

32:30.000 --> 32:31.740
[ Sighs ]

32:39.750 --> 32:41.240
[ Gun cocks ]

32:41.250 --> 32:42.786
Come on, man.
[ Gun cocks ]

32:42.790 --> 32:44.872
Put it down, Kane.

32:44.880 --> 32:48.111
[ Scoffs ]

32:48.120 --> 32:51.749
Greyson McConnell,
humble tavern owner.

32:51.750 --> 32:56.119
You know, if Frank
doesn't hear from me, Grey,

32:56.120 --> 33:00.033
your little friend
is in a very bad situation.

33:00.040 --> 33:02.827
Just put the gun down,
Kane.

33:02.830 --> 33:04.377
Let Denton go,

33:04.380 --> 33:06.996
_ and we can all
just walk away, okay?

33:07.000 --> 33:08.035
All the loot is yours.

33:08.040 --> 33:09.246
Isn't that right, Denton?

33:09.250 --> 33:11.286
He can have it all.
Works for me.

33:11.290 --> 33:13.201
So, what do you want,
Kane?

33:13.210 --> 33:15.781
You want cash to finance
your We on the run?

33:15.790 --> 33:18.327
Or you want to prove a point
and go back to prison?

33:18.330 --> 33:22.664
See, now,
that's the Grey I know --

33:22.670 --> 33:23.739
level-headed.

33:25.040 --> 33:26.917
Put the gun down,
Greyson.

33:26.920 --> 33:29.115
I could solve
so many people's problems

33:29.120 --> 33:30.610
by just pulling
this trigger.

33:30.620 --> 33:33.032
Put it down.

33:41.540 --> 33:43.371
[ Brakes screech lightly,
gearshift clicks ]

33:43.380 --> 33:45.780
[ Sighs ]

33:45.790 --> 33:48.031
Could be staging out of
this warehouse over here.

33:48.040 --> 33:49.701
That's his MD.
He's a tunneler.

33:49.710 --> 33:51.530
Pulled four jobs
that way.

33:51.540 --> 33:53.701
Alright,
let's check it out.
Hold on a second.

33:53.710 --> 33:55.450
Detective Miles Hoffman

33:55.460 --> 33:56.779
requesting Code-3 cover
at Portland Museum.
[ Gunshots ]

33:56.790 --> 33:59.372
Dex, where you going? Stop --
Shots fired! Shots fired!

33:59.380 --> 34:01.610
[The Clash's
"Police On My Back" plays ]

34:06.960 --> 34:08.166
Portland police!

34:08.170 --> 34:09.239
[ Gunshots ]
Denton: Aah!

34:11.120 --> 34:12.417
[ Chamber clicking ]
Well, I'm running

34:12.420 --> 34:13.614
He shot me!

34:13.620 --> 34:15.281
Police on my back,
I've been hiding

34:15.290 --> 34:16.450
You're okay!
You're okay! Relax!
[ Groaning ]

34:16.460 --> 34:17.779
Move. Move.

34:17.790 --> 34:19.109
-Hey, what are you --
-Stay back! Stay back!

34:19.120 --> 34:20.951
Police on my back

34:20.960 --> 34:22.575
And the victim

34:22.580 --> 34:23.956
Well, he won't come back

34:23.960 --> 34:25.996
I been running Monday

34:26.000 --> 34:27.376
Ow! Ahh!
I'm -- I'm sorry.

34:27.380 --> 34:28.415
Dex, I'm sorry.
I screwed up.

34:28.420 --> 34:29.375
Dex: Medic!

34:29.380 --> 34:30.529
He's heavy.

34:30.540 --> 34:31.825
Medic!

34:31.830 --> 34:33.570
Grey: Dex --
Alright, put
your hand underneath.

34:33.580 --> 34:35.571
See if the bullet went
all the way through.

34:35.580 --> 34:37.992
Friday, Saturday, Sunday

34:38.000 --> 34:40.742
What have I done?

34:40.750 --> 34:42.069
-Let me see your hands!
-Hey.

34:42.080 --> 34:44.036
Don't move!
Look, there's
a gunshot wound, okay?

34:44.040 --> 34:45.280
I think
it hit an artery.

34:45.290 --> 34:46.871
We're gonna need medical
down here immediately.

34:46.880 --> 34:48.245
Yes, I'm running

34:48.250 --> 34:50.115
Get down!
Down the railway track

34:50.120 --> 34:51.872
Could you help me?

34:51.880 --> 34:53.245
Police on my back

34:53.250 --> 34:55.161
They will catch me

34:55.170 --> 34:56.740
IfI dare drop back

34:56.750 --> 34:58.320
Won't you give me

34:58.330 --> 35:01.379
All the speed I lack?

35:01.380 --> 35:03.575
What have I done?

35:03.580 --> 35:04.820
[ Groans ]

35:04.830 --> 35:06.991
What have I done?

35:08.080 --> 35:11.413
You know how I can tell
I was born to be a crook?

35:11.420 --> 35:14.878
I missed having guns
pointed at me.

35:14.880 --> 35:16.074
Isn't that sick?

35:20.920 --> 35:24.788
But you're most alive
in that moment.

35:24.790 --> 35:27.076
And now twice in one day.

35:27.080 --> 35:30.208
It makes breaking out worth it
just for this.

35:30.210 --> 35:32.417
You know why I'm glad
you broke out?

35:32.420 --> 35:35.321
So I could be the one
to put a bullet In your head.

35:35.330 --> 35:36.740
[ Sirens wail in distance ]

35:36.750 --> 35:40.242
Darius was my friend.

35:40.250 --> 35:41.740
Yeah, I put
a bullet in his head,

35:41.750 --> 35:45.618
but you served him up,
Detective.

35:45.620 --> 35:47.531
You want to kill me?

35:47.540 --> 35:48.996
You go right ahead.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.070
But it ain't ever gonna
make you feel any better.

35:57.330 --> 35:59.286
What do you want me to do?

35:59.290 --> 36:01.702
Beg for my life,
like Darius did?

36:03.250 --> 36:04.376
Like a bitch?

36:04.380 --> 36:06.780
Miles! Stand down!

36:06.790 --> 36:08.109
[ Breathes sharply ]

36:08.120 --> 36:09.826
Go ahead.

36:15.040 --> 36:16.530
You're not gonna do this.

36:18.670 --> 36:20.911
Look, you know, maybe we do
this tomorrow, man, you know?

36:20.920 --> 36:21.739
Hoffman: We got to go.

36:21.750 --> 36:23.286
I got you.

36:23.290 --> 36:24.666
Trust me. Go.

36:24.670 --> 36:26.240
I'm scared.

36:26.250 --> 36:27.376
You asked for my help.
I gave it to you.

36:27.380 --> 36:28.824
We got to go now.
Just trust me.

36:28.830 --> 36:29.990
I got you.

36:30.000 --> 36:31.115
We got to go. Trust me.

36:31.120 --> 36:32.576
[ Gunshot ]

36:38.000 --> 36:40.707
[ Sirens approaching ]

36:47.000 --> 36:49.207
[ Siren chirps, radio chatter]

36:49.210 --> 36:50.575
Thanks.

36:55.880 --> 36:57.871
Hey.
Hey. You, uh --

36:57.880 --> 36:59.495
You need anything?

36:59.500 --> 37:00.956
A favor.

37:00.960 --> 37:02.666
Of course you do.

37:06.330 --> 37:08.457
Take it easy on Grey.

37:08.460 --> 37:11.167
Do you really know
this guy?

37:11.170 --> 37:13.491
I know enough.

37:15.460 --> 37:17.951
Man: Detective Hoffman?
You got a second?

37:23.790 --> 37:24.575
Man: ...job your team did.

37:24.580 --> 37:26.320
Yes, sir.

37:26.330 --> 37:28.537
I -- I very much
appreciate that.

37:28.540 --> 37:30.167
I want you
to tell Hoffman...

37:30.170 --> 37:33.037
Yep, I would be happy to convey
that to Detective Hoffman.

37:33.040 --> 37:35.611
Very proud
of what you did.

37:35.620 --> 37:37.451
In fact, he's walking
in here right now.

37:37.460 --> 37:39.075
He Jewish, by the way?

37:39.080 --> 37:41.617
No, I don't --
I don't believe he is Jewish,

37:41.620 --> 37:43.997
